Gbgs h. latin 28, Cand. med. dent. i Greifs-v^^ald 30, tysk tandläk. i München 33, svensk tandläk. 34. Egen praktik i Falkenberg sed. 34. Finalist i SM i tennis 42, 44, 45, erövrat SM i tennis 46.
translated: Bramstång, Sven Oskar Johannes, dentist, Falkenberg, born on February 3rd, 1910 in Varberg to Carl B. and Ellen Rohlin. Married in 1943 to Stina Johansson. Children: Kerstin, born in 1946. He took his studentexamen from Gothenburg's Högre Latinläroverk in 1928, graduated with a degree in dental medicine from Greifs-wald in 1930, studied German dentistry in Munich in 1933, and became a Swedish dentist in 1934. He established his own practice in Falkenberg from 1934 onwards. He was a finalist in the Swedish National Championships for tennis in 1942, 1944, and 1945, and won the National Championships in 1946.
